4.Proposed System:
Functional:
In our application an user with either android or windows phone can download apps. First the user needs to register in the sign up page if they want to download the apps. Guest users can only view the apps. This app will guide the user by suggesting good apps along with the reviews and ratings. Once the user logins the app store will show all the respective apps of their OS. User can search the apps based on the category like games, dictionary, music etc. On selecting the app, the user can view the description, reviews, rating and other suggested apps. User can download the app or view other apps to meet their requirements. The user will get notifications about recommended apps.

Non-functional: 
System
Operating System: windows
Ram: 2GB
Hard disk: 500GB
Technical
Tools: Visual Studio
Languages: Java, C#, ASP.net, ADO.net
Database: SQL Server, SQLite













5.Framework Specification:
Architecture Diagram

 


Class diagram
 

 Sequence diagram 
 
Activity diagram
				        
Operational description
	First the user needs to register in the sign up page if they want to download the apps. 
	Once the user logins the app store will show all the respective apps of their OS. 
	User can search the apps based on the category like games, dictionary, music etc. 
	On selecting the app, the user can view the description, reviews, rating and other suggested apps. 
	User can download the app or view other apps to meet their requirements. The user will get notifications about recommended apps.
Constraints/exceptions
	Gathering the original data from the apps is one of the primary constraint.
	Identifying the O.S. and notifying the user regarding the applications and allowing them to install is the major task.

Priorities (degree of importance, difficulty, etc.)
	Developing the application with very attractive and easy to navigate user interface is s of highest priority.
	Gather the information regarding the apps of different O.S is the next step.
	Deploying the web application is the further step.



6.Testcases:
Test Cases For Logins
Test	Input	Actual output	Expected output	Description
Valid login	Valid username& valid password	Login successful	Login successful	Test passed
Invalid login	Invalid username or invalid password	Login not successful	Login not successful	Test passed
Invalid login	Null, null	Fields should not be empty	Fields should not be empty	Test passed

				





Test Cases For User Registration
Test	Input	Received output	Actual output	Description
Valid registration	Valid email id& password & ph.no	Valid registration	Valid registration	Test passed
Invalid registration	Invalid email id	Email id must not contain more than one @	Email id must not contain more than one @	Test passed
Invalid registration	Password=null	Field must not be empty	Field must not be empty	Test passed
Invalid registration	Invalid user name	User name should not contain numbers	User name should not contain numbers	Test passed

	

